<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08053p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08053p">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08053p"> 53(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> les enfant (lazer)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">J&apos;ai m&ecirc;me observ&eacute; un paresseux instruit qui substituait syst&eacute;matiquement le singulier au pluriel pour s&apos;&eacute;viter la peine de tracer un <i>s</i>. Il &eacute;crivait: &ldquo;Les enfant iront aux v&ecirc;pre&rdquo;. <br><font color="green">[I have even seen an educated lazy person who substituted the singular for the plural forms in order to avoid having to write an <i>s</i>. He wrote &ldquo;The infant are going to vesper&rdquo;]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 197</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
